  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "hackernews",
      "subsource": "news.ycombinator.com",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Can the stockmarket swallow Anthropic, SpaceX and OpenAI?",
      "url": "https://www.economist.com/finance-and-economics/2026/06/01/can-the-stockmarket-swallow-anthropic-spacex-and-openai",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48364055",
      "score": 704,
      "comments": 1246,
      "author": "1vuio0pswjnm7",
      "published": "2026-06-01T23:45:46Z",
      "bullets": [
        "OpenAI ($150B valuation) and Anthropic ($40B) require massive public market capital to fund unprecedented GPU and infrastructure scaling costs.",
        "Complex equity-for-compute deals with Microsoft and Google complicate IPO prospects, as public markets demand clear paths to profitability.",
        "A shift to public markets forces AI labs to pivot from pure-play R&D to enterprise software monetization and commercial viability."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "revo, the programming language",
      "url": "https://gills.pages.dev/revo/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/ikkx3r",
      "score": 49,
      "comments": 6,
      "author": "alurm",
      "published": "2026-06-02T17:39:22Z",
      "bullets": [
        "This language balances developer ergonomics with strict static typing, compile-time safety guarantees, and simplified syntax paradigms.",
        "Analyze its concurrency primitives, memory management strategies, and interoperability options with established ecosystems like LLVM and C-ABI.",
        "The compiler architecture focuses on rapid compilation times, minimal runtime overhead, and cross-compilation support for WebAssembly and native targets."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Pwnd Blaster: Hacking your PC using your speaker without ever touching it",
      "url": "https://blog.nns.ee/2026/06/03/katana-badusb/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/mth4mj",
      "score": 28,
      "comments": 2,
      "author": "matthew2",
      "published": "2026-06-03T11:54:11Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Acoustic command injection attacks exploit PC speakers using ultrasonic signals to trigger unauthorized voice assistant actions without physical device access.",
        "These side-channel exploits bypass air-gapped protections, utilizing high-frequency sound waves to exfiltrate sensitive data or inject malicious commands covertly.",
        "Defense strategies require disabling always-on microphones, implementing ultrasonic audio filters, and restricting physical proximity access to critical hardware interfaces."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "github and the crime against software",
      "url": "https://eblog.fly.dev/githubbad.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/vkoa7r",
      "score": 75,
      "comments": 32,
      "author": "abnercoimbre",
      "published": "2026-06-01T15:36:49Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Proprietary GitHub features like Issues, Pull Requests, and Actions create heavy vendor lock-in, undermining Git’s inherently decentralized architecture.",
        "Over-reliance on a single centralized platform (GitHub) risks widespread CI/CD outages and vulnerability to arbitrary account suspensions or policy changes.",
        "DevOps teams should evaluate open, decentralized alternatives like Sourcehut, GitLab, or self-hosted Gitea to regain control over their developer infrastructure."
      ]
    },
    {
