      "score": 208,
      "comments": 183,
      "author": "berkeleyjunk",
      "published": "2026-06-02T18:09:53Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Morningstar's $780B valuation, down 50% from IPO targets, signals shifting investor expectations for capital-intensive, deep-tech infrastructure companies.",
        "Future upside depends heavily on Starlink's global subscription growth and Starship achieving regular, low-cost orbital launch cadence.",
        "The appraisal reflects broader market caution regarding regulatory hurdles, orbital debris mitigation, and long-term commercial monetization of space."
      ]
